<subSubSection pageNumber="576" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="576">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="576">Note:</emphasis>
Fawcett &amp; Rendle (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="576">Fl. Jamaica</emphasis>
3: 175. 1914) stated &quot;Type in Herb. Linn.&quot; and Turrill (in Turrill &amp; Milne-Redhead, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="576">
Fl. Trop. E. Africa, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Caryophyllaceae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
: 11. 1956) made a similar statement. Later, Mizushima (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="576">J. Jap. Bot.</emphasis>
32: 70. 1957) explicitly chose 109.1 (LINN) as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
and was followed by others. However, this sheet, as noted by Howard (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="576">Fl. Lesser Antilles</emphasis>
4: 211. 1988), is a post-1753 addition to the Linnaean herbarium, is not original material, and is not eligible for lectotypification of the name.
</paragraph>
